Common Application Guide

Wondering which colleges on your list accept the Common Application? Enter a college name below to find out!

CollegeData’s Common App Guide features:

  • Application deadlines, fees, and requirements for more than 700 Common App schools on CollegeData
  • Early Action and Early Decision deadlines
  • Requirements for essays, additional writing supplements, and letters of recommendation

Key to the Guide

E: College requires the Common Application essay; WS: College requires a Writing Supplement in addition to or in place of the Common Application essay; E, WS: College requires both the Common Application essay and a Writing Supplement; CR: Counselor Recommendation required; TR: Teacher Recommendation required; OR: Other/non-academic recommendation required; School Report: a description of your high school provided by your counselor, usually sent with your transcript; Midyear Report: Grades from the first term of senior year.

Data represents Common Application Colleges listed on CollegeData as of October 2019.

Thanks for completing the CollegeData sign up process!

CollegeData is committed to supporting you on your path to college, providing you with a responsible, reliable service to help you fulfill your college dreams.

CollegeData is a service of 1st Financial Bank USA.

CollegeData Dollars are points you earn by completing certain CollegeData activities

Four of the best ways to earn CollegeData Dollars:

  1. Complete your Admissions Profile.
  2. Add colleges to your College Choices.
  3. Update your Admissions Statuses.
  4. Use the College Match tool.

What are CollegeData Dollars (CD$)?

CollegeData Dollars (CD$) are points you earn by completing certain CollegeData activities. The maximum number of CD$ you can redeem is 5000. Once you have earned at least 2500 CD$, you can redeem them for $25, which will be provided to you on a Loyalty Card, and once you earn another 2500 CD$, you can redeem those CD$ for a second $25, which will also be provided to you on a Loyalty Card.

Earn points and redeem them for U.S. Dollars

Complete certain CollegeData activities (for example, signing up, starting your Admissions Profile, searching for colleges, calculating your chances for admission, searching for scholarships, updating your Profile with your admission decisions). Each activity is worth a specific amount of points (CD$). You can redeem the points you earn for U.S. Dollars that will be issued to you in the form of a 1st Financial Bank USA Loyalty Mastercard®.

How do I earn CollegeData Dollars?

You can earn CD$ by completing certain CollegeData activities. As soon as you sign up and activate your CollegeData account, explore CollegeData and begin completing CollegeData activities to earn points.

Here is a full list of CollegeData activities for which you may earn CD$ and the number of CD$ you can earn by completing each activity.*

Activity CD$
Sign up for CollegeData 2000
Provide additional information at sign up 250
Search for colleges and save one to your Data Locker 250

The CD$ Program is a loyalty rewards program for your personal use only. Commercial use is prohibited. To be eligible to participate in the CD$ Program, you must be at least 16 years of age, a high school sophomore, junior or senior or college freshman, and a U.S. citizen or permanent U.S. resident with a U.S. mailing address. Eligibility criteria may change at any time in our sole and exclusive discretion. If you are between the age of 16 and the age of majority in your state of residence, you may only participate in the CD$ Program with the consent and supervision of your parent or legal guardian. The program is not intended for or targeted to anyone under the age of 16.
